This paper is primarily focused on multimedia streaming over HTTP, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also investigates and evaluates the usage of advanced transport options, which suggests that it could belong to the network and internet architecture (cs.NI) or distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses emerging developments within both protocol layers, which could also place it in the social and information networks (cs.SN) or network science and engineering (cs.NE) categories.
